725927f-a.title: Queens: 159th Street - Beaver Road
725927f-a.text:
94-27 159th Street, east side, south of Beaver Road,
showing St. Monicas Hall, belonging to St. Monicas Roman
Catholic Church which fronts on 160th Street. The congre-
gationlsocial activities are conducted here.
P. L. Sperr  March 30, 1932

725922f-a.title: Queens: 159th Street - Beaver Road
725922f-a.text:
94-09 and 94-15 159th Street, at and adjoining the S.E.
corner of Beaver Road, just below the Long lIsland Railroad
tracks, showing two old frame houses of eighteanth century con--
struction. Aoross the roof is St. Monicas Roman Catholic Church
on 160th Street; on the right is St. Monica's Hall. 159th Street
was known as Prospect Street and Medford Street. Beaver Road, at
this point, has not yet been cut through.
P. L. Sperr  March 30, 1932
NO REPRODUCTIONS
